#. <section class="sutta" id="sn51.15"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn51.15:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 51"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 51"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn51.15:0.2"
msgid "2. Pāsādakampanavagga"
msgstr "2. Shaking the Stilt Longhouse"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 15. Uṇṇābhabrāhmaṇasutta → brāhmaṇasuttaṃ (bj) | brāhmaṇa (pts1)
msgctxt "sn51.15:0.3"
msgid "15. Uṇṇābhabrāhmaṇasutta"
msgstr "15. The Brahmin Uṇṇābha"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi5.272"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn51.15:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

msgctxt "sn51.15:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ āyasmā ānando kosambiyaṃ viharati ghositārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time Venerable Ānanda was staying near Kosambi, in Ghosita’s "
"Monastery."

msgctxt "sn51.15:1.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho uṇṇābho brāhmaṇo yenāyasmā ānando tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā "
"āyasmatā ānandena saddhiṃ sammodi."
msgstr ""
"Then Uṇṇābha the brahmin went up to Venerable Ānanda, and exchanged "
"greetings with him."

msgctxt "sn51.15:1.4"
msgid ""
"Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ "
"nisinno kho uṇṇābho brāhmaṇo āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one "
"side and said to him:"

msgctxt "sn51.15:1.5"
msgid ""
"“kimatthiyaṃ nu kho, bho ānanda, samaṇe gotame brahmacariyaṃ vussatī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Master Ānanda, what’s the purpose of living the spiritual life with the "
"ascetic Gotama?”"

msgctxt "sn51.15:1.6"
msgid "“Chandappahānatthaṃ kho, brāhmaṇa, bhagavati brahmacariyaṃ vussatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“The purpose of living the spiritual life under the Buddha, brahmin, is to "
"give up desire.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn51.15:2.1"
msgid ""
"“Atthi pana, bho ānanda, maggo atthi paṭipadā etassa chandassa pahānāyā”ti?"
msgstr "“But is there a path and a practice for giving up that desire?”"

msgctxt "sn51.15:2.2"
msgid ""
"“Atthi kho, brāhmaṇa, maggo, atthi paṭipadā etassa chandassa pahānāyā”ti."
msgstr "“There is.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn51.15:3.1"
msgid ""
"“Katamo pana, bho ānanda, maggo katamā paṭipadā etassa chandassa pahānāyā”ti?"
msgstr "“What is that path?”"

msgctxt "sn51.15:3.2"
msgid ""
"“Idha, brāhmaṇa, bhikkhu chandasamādhippadhānasaṅkhārasamannāgataṃ "
"iddhipādaṃ bhāveti, "
msgstr ""
"“It’s when a mendicant develops the basis of psychic power that has "
"immersion due to enthusiasm … "

msgctxt "sn51.15:3.3"
msgid "vīriyasamādhi … pe …"
msgstr "energy …"

msgctxt "sn51.15:3.4"
msgid "cittasamādhi …"
msgstr "mental development …"

msgctxt "sn51.15:3.5"
msgid "vīmaṃsāsamādhippadhānasaṅkhārasamannāgataṃ iddhipādaṃ bhāveti—"
msgstr "inquiry, and active effort."

msgctxt "sn51.15:3.6"
msgid "ayaṃ kho, brāhmaṇa, maggo ayaṃ paṭipadā etassa chandassa pahānāyā”ti."
msgstr "This is the path and the practice for giving up that desire.”"

# See BB on readings.
#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi5.273"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn51.15:4.1"
msgid "“Evaṃ sante, bho ānanda, santakaṃ hoti no asantakaṃ."
msgstr "“This being the case, Master Ānanda, the path is endless, not finite."

msgctxt "sn51.15:4.2"
msgid "Chandeneva chandaṃ pajahissatīti—netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati”."
msgstr "For it’s not possible to give up desire by means of desire.”"

msgctxt "sn51.15:4.3"
msgid ""
"“Tena hi, brāhmaṇa, taññevettha paṭipucchissāmi. Yathā te khameyya tathā taṃ "
"byākareyyāsi."
msgstr ""
"“Well then, brahmin, I’ll ask you about this in return, and you can answer "
"as you like."

msgctxt "sn51.15:4.4"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, brāhmaṇa, "
msgstr "What do you think, brahmin? "

msgctxt "sn51.15:4.5"
msgid "ahosi te pubbe chando ‘ārāmaṃ gamissāmī’ti?"
msgstr "Have you ever had a desire to walk to the park,"

msgctxt "sn51.15:4.6"
msgid "Tassa te ārāmagatassa yo tajjo chando so paṭippassaddho”ti?"
msgstr "but when you arrived at the park, the corresponding desire faded away?”"

msgctxt "sn51.15:4.7"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bho”."
msgstr "“Yes, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn51.15:4.8"
msgid "“Ahosi te pubbe vīriyaṃ ‘ārāmaṃ gamissāmī’ti?"
msgstr "“Have you ever had the energy to walk to the park,"

msgctxt "sn51.15:4.9"
msgid "Tassa te ārāmagatassa yaṃ tajjaṃ vīriyaṃ taṃ paṭippassaddhan”ti?"
msgstr "but when you arrived at the park, the corresponding energy faded away?”"

msgctxt "sn51.15:4.10"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bho”."
msgstr "“Yes, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn51.15:4.11"
msgid "“Ahosi te pubbe cittaṃ ‘ārāmaṃ gamissāmī’ti?"
msgstr "“Have you ever had the idea to walk to the park,"

msgctxt "sn51.15:4.12"
msgid "Tassa te ārāmagatassa yaṃ tajjaṃ cittaṃ taṃ paṭippassaddhan”ti?"
msgstr "but when you arrived at the park, the corresponding idea faded away?”"

msgctxt "sn51.15:4.13"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bho”."
msgstr "“Yes, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn51.15:4.14"
msgid "“Ahosi te pubbe vīmaṃsā ‘ārāmaṃ gamissāmī’ti?"
msgstr "“Have you ever inquired regarding a walk to the park,"

msgctxt "sn51.15:4.15"
msgid "Tassa te ārāmagatassa yā tajjā vīmaṃsā sā paṭippassaddhā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"but when you arrived at the park, the corresponding inquiry faded away?”"

msgctxt "sn51.15:4.16"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bho”."
msgstr "“Yes, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
#. VAR: arahattappatte → arahatte patte (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "sn51.15:5.1"
msgid ""
"“Evameva kho, brāhmaṇa, yo so bhikkhu arahaṃ khīṇāsavo vusitavā katakaraṇīyo "
"ohitabhāro anuppattasadattho parikkhīṇabhavasaṃyojano sammadaññāvimutto, "
"tassa yo pubbe chando ahosi arahattappattiyā, arahattappatte yo tajjo chando "
"so paṭippassaddho;"
msgstr ""
"“In the same way, take a mendicant who is perfected—with defilements ended, "
"who has completed the spiritual journey, done what had to be done, laid down "
"the burden, achieved their own true goal, utterly ended the fetters of "
"rebirth, and is rightly freed through enlightenment. They formerly had the "
"desire to attain perfection, but when they attained perfection the "
"corresponding desire faded away."

msgctxt "sn51.15:5.2"
msgid ""
"yaṃ pubbe vīriyaṃ ahosi arahattappattiyā, arahattappatte yaṃ tajjaṃ vīriyaṃ "
"taṃ paṭippassaddhaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"They formerly had the energy to attain perfection, but when they attained "
"perfection the corresponding energy faded away."

msgctxt "sn51.15:5.3"
msgid ""
"yaṃ pubbe cittaṃ ahosi arahattappattiyā, arahattappatte yaṃ tajjaṃ cittaṃ "
"taṃ paṭippassaddhaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"They formerly had the idea to attain perfection, but when they attained "
"perfection the corresponding idea faded away."

msgctxt "sn51.15:5.4"
msgid ""
"yā pubbe vīmaṃsā ahosi arahattappattiyā, arahattappatte yā tajjā vīmaṃsā sā "
"paṭippassaddhā."
msgstr ""
"They formerly inquired regarding attaining perfection, but when they "
"attained perfection the corresponding inquiry faded away."

msgctxt "sn51.15:5.5"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, brāhmaṇa, "
msgstr "What do you think, brahmin? "

msgctxt "sn51.15:5.6"
msgid "iti evaṃ sante, santakaṃ vā hoti no asantakaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr "This being the case, is the path endless or finite?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn51.15:6.1"
msgid "“Addhā, bho ānanda, evaṃ sante, santakaṃ hoti no asantakaṃ."
msgstr ""
"“Clearly, Master Ānanda, this being the case, the path is finite, not "
"endless."

msgctxt "sn51.15:6.2"
msgid "Abhikkantaṃ, bho ānanda, abhikkantaṃ, bho ānanda."
msgstr "Excellent, Master Ānanda! Excellent!"

msgctxt "sn51.15:6.3"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bho ānanda, nikkujjitaṃ vā ukkujjeyya, paṭicchannaṃ vā "
"vivareyya, mūḷhassa vā maggaṃ ācikkheyya, andhakāre vā telapajjotaṃ dhāreyya:"
" ‘cakkhumanto rūpāni dakkhantī’ti; evamevaṃ bhotā ānandena anekapariyāyena "
"dhammo pakāsito."
msgstr ""
"As if he were righting the overturned, or revealing the hidden, or pointing "
"out the path to the lost, or lighting a lamp in the dark so people with good "
"eyes can see what’s there, Master Ānanda has made the teaching clear in many "
"ways."

msgctxt "sn51.15:6.4"
msgid ""
"Esāhaṃ, bho ānanda, taṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāmi dhammañca "
"bhikkhusaṅghañca."
msgstr ""
"I go for refuge to Master Gotama, to the teaching, and to the mendicant "
"Saṅgha."

msgctxt "sn51.15:6.5"
msgid ""
"Upāsakaṃ maṃ bhavaṃ ānando dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan”ti."
msgstr ""
"From this day forth, may Master Ānanda remember me as a lay follower who has "
"gone for refuge for life.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn51.15:6.6"
msgid "Pañcamaṃ."
msgstr ""
